JOHANNESBURG - South African bonds may deteriorate further if Moody s downgrades the country s sovereign rating.Despite being resilient after last week s downgrades from S&P and Fitch, the market will get tighter for the bond indices.Government needs to borrow money, and it does so by selling bonds to the private sector.READ: What junk status means for South AfricansInvestors are quite happy to buy government bonds because they bring a guaranteed rate of returns.But a government can be seen as a possible defaulter when its investment grade is downgraded.* Watch the full video report by Motheo Khoaripe in the gallery above.eNCA